title: DPM, Canadian FM discuss bilateral ties
content:
NEW YORK, Sep 22 (APP): Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Minister Senator Muhammad Ishaq Dar Monday met with Foreign Minister of Canada Anita Anand on the sidelines of 80th United Nations General Assembly session in New York. They acknowledged the positive trajectory of Pakistan-Canada relations, agreed to further strengthen economic and trade ties and recognized the vital role of the Pakistani diaspora in Canada.
